<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="smtpmx.php" src="/usr/local/Cellar/php55/5.5.5/lib/php/Mail/smtpmx.php"><import line="50" module="Net/SMTP.php" /><scope classrefs="Mail" doc="SMTP MX implementation of the PEAR Mail interface. Requires the Net_SMTP class.&#10;&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@author  gERD Schaufelberger &lt;gerd@php-tools.net&gt;&#10;@package Mail&#10;@version $Revision: 294747 $" ilk="class" line="61" lineend="502" name="Mail_smtpmx"><variable citdl="Net_SMTP" doc="SMTP connection object.&#10;&#10;@var object&#10;@access private" line="69" name="_smtp" /><variable citdl="integer" doc="The port the SMTP server is on.&#10;@var integer&#10;@see getservicebyname()" line="76" name="port" /><variable citdl="string" doc="Hostname or domain that will be sent to the remote SMTP server in the&#10;HELO / EHLO message.&#10;&#10;@var string&#10;@see posix_uname()" line="85" name="mailname" /><variable citdl="integer" doc="SMTP connection timeout value.  NULL indicates no timeout.&#10;&#10;@var integer" line="92" name="timeout" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="use either PEAR:Net_DNS or getmxrr&#10;&#10;@var boolean" line="99" name="withNetDns" /><variable citdl="Net_DNS_Resolver" doc="PEAR:Net_DNS_Resolver&#10;&#10;@var object" line="106" name="resolver" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="Whether to use VERP or not. If not a boolean, the string value&#10;will be used as the VERP separators.&#10;&#10;@var mixed boolean or string" line="114" name="verp" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="Whether to use VRFY or not.&#10;&#10;@var boolean $vrfy" line="121" name="vrfy" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="Switch to test mode - don't send emails for real&#10;&#10;@var boolean $debug" line="128" name="test" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="Turn on Net_SMTP debugging?&#10;&#10;@var boolean $peardebug" line="135" name="debug" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="internal error codes&#10;&#10;translate internal error identifier to PEAR-Error codes and human&#10;readable messages.&#10;&#10;@var boolean $debug&#10;@todo as I need unique error-codes to identify what exactly went wrond&#10;      I did not use intergers as it should be. Instead I added a &quot;namespace&quot;&#10;      for each code. This avoids conflicts with error codes from different&#10;      classes. How can I use unique error codes and stay conform with PEAR?" line="190" name="errorCode" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor.&#10;&#10;Instantiates a new Mail_smtp:: object based on the parameters&#10;passed in. It looks for the following parameters:&#10;    mailname    The name of the local mail system (a valid hostname which matches the reverse lookup)&#10;    port        smtp-port - the default comes from getservicebyname() and should work fine&#10;    timeout     The SMTP connection timeout. Defaults to 30 seconds.&#10;    vrfy        Whether to use VRFY or not. Defaults to false.&#10;    verp        Whether to use VERP or not. Defaults to false.&#10;    test        Activate test mode? Defaults to false.&#10;    debug       Activate SMTP and Net_DNS debug mode? Defaults to false.&#10;    netdns      whether to use PEAR:Net_DNS or the PHP build in function getmxrr, default is true&#10;&#10;If a parameter is present in the $params array, it replaces the&#10;default.&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@param array Hash containing any parameters different from the&#10;             defaults.&#10;@see _Mail_smtpmx()" ilk="function" line="214" lineend="238" name="__construct" signature="__construct($params)"><variable ilk="argument" line="214" name="params" /><variable citdl="posix_uname()" line="221" name="uname" /></scope><variable citdl="params" line="228" name="_port" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor wrapper for PHP4&#10;&#10;@access public&#10;@param array Hash containing any parameters different from the defaults&#10;@see __construct()" ilk="function" line="247" lineend="251" name="Mail_smtpmx" signature="Mail_smtpmx($params)"><variable ilk="argument" line="2